        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2682175989" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer120933016551346641">Mandie and her friends unravel the mystery of missing gold after a late-night train wreck and some &quot;ghostly&quot; robbers. Was Uncle Ned right about gold being bad luck for the Cherokee people?<br/><br/>This story actually had a lot more going on than the last two, and they had quite a bit! Still able to be a kid&apos;s story, so nothing was too intense or confusing, but there were more than just one simple plot line to understand. This mixed with the added intrigue and suspense (and constant reminder of trusting G</span>
  <span id="freeText120933016551346641" style="display:none">Mandie and her friends unravel the mystery of missing gold after a late-night train wreck and some "ghostly" robbers. Was Uncle Ned right about gold being bad luck for the Cherokee people?<br /><br />This story actually had a lot more going on than the last two, and they had quite a bit! Still able to be a kid's story, so nothing was too intense or confusing, but there were more than just one simple plot line to understand. This mixed with the added intrigue and suspense (and constant reminder of trusting God) makes it perfect for readers of all ages!</span>
